really odd experience. they messed up my order (one sub was correct, the other was wrong), so i called to get what i ordered (the one sub). they said cool, sorry we will send it. a different guy calls me and asks if i want a free cookie or chips - which was very nice. i said, 'sure, not necessary, but a cookie would be good.' then i get another call from a lady asking if i can return the first sandwich. i said 'that's fine, but i took a bite of it which is when i realized it's the wrong sandwich.' she said 'that's fine; just return it.' so strange. i feel like they think i tried to scam them? ... you are the ones who tried to scam me out of my guac and cheese! the second sandwich still was wrong, but i was hungry, so i just accepted it. two thumbs down. delivery guy was very nice though.

(I wanted to give the owner a chance to address the issue) but Russel #theowner was too busy. I don’t recommend this place for anyone. I went in to this location, placed my order of the veggie sandwich and went home. When I got back and opened my sandwich I realized that they had forgotten the avocado spread (which is pretty important on just a veggie sandwich). When I told them they asked if I could come back in to get a new one and I explained that my car is parked a distance and that I would prefer if they could drop it off. We got off the phone and as I was waiting for the new sandwich to come, I gave the original sandwich to my roommate. They called about 10 mins later asking if I could return the old sandwich and I explained the situation and mentioned they didn’t tell me anything about returning the sandwich on the original phone call and they said okay. A FULL hour and a half later I get a call that they are here with my sandwich. When I went to go eat it I saw that ONCE AGAIN they forgot the avocado spread. That is absolutely ridiculous and I will not be returning to this location.
